Pre-heat your #oven to 220 degrees. Peel and dice the @onion{1}(peeled and diced) and @carrot{1}(peeled and diced), dice the @celery stick{1.5}(diced) and @garlic cloves{2}(diced). Peel and slice the @potatoes{2}(peeled and sliced into discs less than ½cm thick) into discs less than ½cm thick.

Heat a tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on a medium-low heat. Cook the onion, carrot, celery and garlic. Add the @bay leaf{1} and your @thyme{3}(leaves stripped from stalks). Pinch the thyme stalk between your fingers and run your fingers along it to strip off the leaves. After around ~{5%minutes} the ingredients will have softened up.

Add in the @baby spinach{2%handfuls} and cook it for a couple of minutes until it has wilted.

Drain and rinse the @organic lentils{1%100g} and stir them into the onion mixture along with the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Let the mixture bubble away until you have a nice thick sauce.

Once the water from the sauce has disappeared, stir through all of the @ricotta cheese{250%g} until you have a smooth sauce and then take the pan off the heat.

Lightly grease an #ovenproof dish{} and place a layer of potatoes in the bottom. Layer half of your lentil mixture on top and cover this with another layer of potatoes. Put on the other half of the lentil mixture and one last layer of potatoes. Bake with a lid on for ~{30%minutes}.

Give the kitchen a quick tidy and put your feet up until dinner is ready.

After 30 mins, if you can slide a #knife{} easily into the potatoes then they are cooked. If not, give them another ~{5%minutes}. Once they are cooked, turn off the oven and pre-heat the grill to high. Sprinkle the @hard Italian style cheese{2%tbsp}(grated) on top of your moussaka. Put it under the grill until it browns off.

Serve the moussaka on plates and enjoy!

> For this recipe we wanted to create something healthy and hearty to warm you from the inside out. After rigorous taste testing down at the Fresh Farm, let us introduce you to our spin on a traditional Moussaka. Though it'll take a little longer to make, once it's in the oven, kick back with a glass of wine and simply relax...